## Time to Wake Up from the Sports Trance

Modern sports aren't just games; they're a festering distraction designed to siphon energy and dollars from the masses. From cheering strangers in imported jerseys to betting against insurmountable odds, the system preys on loyalty while delivering little in return. Like the Romans who ignored their empire's collapse amid Colosseum cheers, today's fans risk overlooking real-world priorities.

It's time to question the obsession. Redirect that passion toward community, family, or personal growth. Sports may entertain, but at what cost? The rot runs deep—don't let it consume you.
